sinopsis: Paul Atreides unites with the Fremen and begins a spiritual and martial journey to become Muad'dib...
The story of scientist J. Robert Oppenheimer and his role in the development of the atomic bomb.
A doting father and his six-year-old daughter find their lives taking a dramatic turn when the mother, who was separated from them, inadvertently re-enters their world.
A female race car driver, is pushed to her limits when a deranged fanboy, who is obsessed with her, begins to stalk and torment her after she rejects him.
A sailing holiday spirals out of control when a teenage daughter uncovers the dark past of her mother's new boyfriend.
An artist grieving the loss of his famous writer husband takes his two best friends on a trip to Paris, where they unpack messy secrets and hard truths.

Someone is blackmailing the CIA by assassinating foreign journalists and making it look like the agency is responsible. As the world begins to unite against the U.S., the CIA must lure its most brilliant – and rebellious – operative out of retirement, forcing him to confront his checkered past while unraveling an international conspiracy.
The chance meeting in Switzerland of a woman and a former lover after a nine-year separation rekindles their romance.

titulo: Race for Glory: Audi vs Lancia
sinopsis: Inspired by true events that occurred during the fierce rivalry between Germany (Audi) and Italy (Lancia) at the 1983 Rally World Championships.

Thomas Kaiser inherits an ancestral mansion that has been in his family for generations - only to learn that he has also inherited an ancient curse stemming back to the Crusades. Forced into his new role as 'protector', the guardian appointed to keep the evil demons in the house at bay, Thomas must unravel the mystery of the house, while struggling to awaken the beautiful Briar Rose, held captive in a terrifying netherworld seen previously in his dreams.

Italy 1609. Michelangelo Merisi, better known as Caravaggio, is on the run after being sentenced to death for the murder of a rival in love. Pope Paul V orders a secret Vatican investigation into Caravaggio to decide whether to grant him the clemency for which he has petitioned. The Investigator, known as The Shadow, begins his inquiry which will lead him to discover the conflicting vices and virtues of the great painter whose life - or death - lies in his hands.
A financial whiz (Matthew Broderick) goes to Buzzsaw, Calif., to get his stepsister's (Jennifer Jason Leigh) money back from two con men.
On October 13, 1972, Uruguayan Air Force Flight 571, chartered to fly a rugby team to Chile, crashes into a glacier in the heart of the Andes.

Steve liked his job, his car, his friends and his girlfriend. Then his unemployment benefits were cut, the government cracked-down on hoon driving and tax evasion, he lost his girl and his best friend... what else could go wrong?! Plenty!
The story of Captain Balram Singh Mehta of India's 45 Cavalry regiment who, along with his siblings, fought on the eastern front during the Indo-Pakistani War of 1971.
An art dealer wants to get married to a young woman. The problem is, her sister wants him too. To solve the problem, he invents his own twin brother.

titulo: And Starring Pancho Villa as Himself
sinopsis: In 1914, the Mexican revolutionary Pancho Villa invites studios to shoot his battles to raise funds for the war. He works with Frank Thayer of the Mutual Film Company and they make the movie "The Life of General Villa".
A writer, haunted by his past, retreats to a remote cabin in the woods where he hopes to find inspiration but instead uncovers a dark secret that threatens his sanity and his life.
An American backpacker travels to Ireland where she finds herself immersed in an ancient pagan ritual and a fight for her life.
A group of teenage girls in a small town form a rock band and navigate the challenges of adolescence, friendship, and fame.
A comedy about a group of friends whose lives are intertwined through their endless and often hilarious group chat conversations.
During a summer vacation, three boys and a girl search for a lost treasure. The reward has been offered by an old man, who needs the money to save a boy's life.
In the near future, a young woman discovers a revolutionary technology that allows people to relive their memories, but soon finds out it has a dark side.
A provocative and unapologetic comedy special from Roseanne Barr, addressing her career, controversies, and a wide range of current topics.

titulo: Mr Bates vs The Post Office: The Real Story
sinopsis: A documentary exploring the true story behind the British Post Office scandal, where hundreds of sub-postmasters were wrongly accused of theft, fraud, and false accounting due to a faulty IT system.

Ambitious young journalist C.J. Nicholas is investigating shady District Attorney Martin Hunter. To trap Hunter, C.J. frames himself for a murder he didn't commit, with help from his friend. But when his friend is killed, C.J. finds himself in a race against time to find the evidence that will exonerate him and expose Hunter.

Confronting a devastating diagnosis, a woman embarks on a journey to her childhood village with her husband, seeking to relive cherished memories before she loses them forever. Along the way, she reconnects with her childhood sweetheart, leading to a poignant exploration of love, loss, and the past.
A detective haunted by a personal tragedy must delve into the complex emotions of a murder case where the lines between victim and perpetrator blur, forcing him to confront his own demons.

A single woman in her thirties, surrounded by her closest friends, navigates the complexities of love, desire, and societal expectations as she embarks on a quest for sexual fulfillment and personal happiness.
A true-crime documentary detailing the rise and fall of Centra Tech, a cryptocurrency company whose founders perpetrated a massive fraud, conning investors out of millions.
The story of PVC awardee Indian soldier Capt. Vikram Batra, who shot to fame and became a household name during the Kargil War in 1999.
An alien abductee undergoes a series of intense interviews and hypnotic regressions to recall his encounters, revealing a terrifying and complex extraterrestrial agenda.
A young Boston priest rising through the ranks of the Catholic Church an American of Irish descent faces bigotry, his own personal crises, and worldly temptations.
An aspiring director targets a ruthless gangster for a film script, but his discreet attempts to research the man's life land him in a series of dangerous, unforeseen situations.

A normal family, dad Ray, mum Judith, and their two teenage children, are subjected to the pressures of modern life as Ray is made redundant and his efforts to get a new job prove fruitless. He decides to document their lives with a camcorder in the hope of winning a TV competition and soon his behaviour turns violent and abusive.
In a post-apocalyptic future, the warrior Kenshiro wanders a barren wasteland, seeking to rescue his love from his rival and bring justice to the oppressed.

A woman inherits a charming old inn from a distant relative, only to discover it holds dark secrets and a history of mysterious disappearances. As she tries to renovate and reopen the inn, she uncovers a sinister plot.
A married woman finds herself drawn into a passionate and dangerous affair with a younger man, leading to a complex web of lies, desire, and betrayal that threatens to unravel her life.

titulo: 1898: Our Last Men in the Philippines
sinopsis: In 1898, a Spanish garrison heroically defended Baler (Philippines) for 337 days after Spain had already surrendered and lost the Philippines to the USA.

A Venezuelan couple moving to the US with approved visas is taken to the secondary inspection room at the Newark airport, where border agents subject them to an unpleasant inspection process and a psychologically grueling interrogation.

titulo: All Dirt Roads Taste of Salt
sinopsis: A lyrical, decades-spanning exploration across a woman's life in Mississippi, the film is an ode to the generations of people, places, and ineffable moments that shape us.
This animated motion comic prequel to the film Inception details how Cobb, Arthur and Nash were enlisted by Cobol Engineering to perform an inception on Mr. Kaneda.

When an entitled basketball star is suspended from his university team, he is sent to an isolated and unconventional basketball camp. He must rediscover his passion for the game and learn what it truly means to be a warrior.

An old dying Gypsy king Tsetse, passes his leadership to his unwilling grandson, Dave. Dave's father, is angry and jealous that he was passed over. He seeks to kill Dave and take the title of king for himself.

A woman grappling with a terminal illness finds unexpected solace and a chance for healing when she reconnects with a childhood friend who introduces her to alternative therapies and a new perspective on life.
A group of strangers find their lives intersecting in a multi-story parking garage during a city-wide lockdown, forcing them to confront their fears, secrets, and each other.
A cynical workaholic woman rediscovers the magic of Christmas when she's forced to spend the holidays in a small, festive town helping her estranged aunt save the local Christmas festival.
When a widow discovers her recently deceased husband's invention – an elixir that makes the drinker look young again – she shares it with her two best friends.

Set during a bitter 1964 Massachusetts winter, young secretary Eileen becomes enchanted by Rebecca Saint John, the glamorous new counselor at the prison where she works. Their budding friendship takes a twisted turn when Rebecca reveals a dark secret — throwing Eileen onto a sinister path.

When their family is shattered by a rival gang, two sisters Keira and Kelly are divided. As they are thrust into the gritty underworld of Sydney's street fighting, they must overcome their differences to unite and seek vengeance for their family.
A Templar Knight is sent to New York to stop a demon from retrieving a key that will unleash Hell on Earth.
A young mother takes a job with a childless couple to make ends meet, unaware that she is entering a world of unimaginable evil.
A group of ex-servicemen are hired by a wealthy man to take part in a jährlisch event held on his private island: A hunting game. What they don't know, is that they are the ones being hunted.
A young boy is drawn into a dangerous conflict when he discovers that his new home is a portal to other dimensions.
Three individuals venture into the remote wilderness of the Allegheny National Forest to shoot a Bigfoot film when they are confronted with the reality that they are not alone.

A legendary hitman known only as "Fable" is ordered by his boss to live a normal life as a civilian in Osaka for one year without killing anyone. Under the alias Akira Sato, he tries to adapt to an ordinary existence with his partner Yoko, who poses as his sister.

High school senior Nicole is determined to become valedictorian, but she faces stiff competition from a few of her classmates. When one of her competitors is attacked, Nicole becomes the prime suspect.

As the clock counted down to the 21st century, the world faced a potential technological catastrophe: the Y2K bug. This documentary explores the global panic and the massive effort to prevent a digital meltdown, using entirely archival footage from the era.
A Ukrainian immigrant mother and her nine-year-old son find refuge in Germany with her lover, but their new life is complicated by simmering tensions and a hidden rivalry.

Dave Chappelle returns to Netflix for his latest stand-up comedy special, 'The Dreamer.' Filmed in his hometown of Washington, D.C., Chappelle shares his unique observations on life, fame, and the world around him.
A deep dive into the mind of Jeffrey Dahmer through the eyes of those who knew him or were involved in his case, exploring the chilling details of his crimes and the aftermath.
Two very different Santas discover that the spirit of Christmas is about more than just presents when they're forced to team up during a bank heist on Christmas Eve.

A group of rebels on the ice planet Hoth must defend their secret base from an impending Imperial attack. This fan film explores the bravery and sacrifice of those fighting for freedom in a galaxy far, far away.
A struggling small-town gas station attendant and aspiring singer, Jodi, is driven to desperate measures after a fatal crime. Her life takes a dark turn as she gets entangled with a dangerous family.

titulo: Evil Among Us: The Golden State Killer
sinopsis: A documentary that delves into the decades-long hunt for one of California's most notorious serial killers, the Golden State Killer, examining the case's impact on victims and the innovative investigative techniques that finally led to an arrest.
Adventurer Jeff Drake and his sidekick Kelly go in search of a pirate's buried treasure on a remote island, facing rival treasure hunters and other dangers along the way in this 15-chapter serial.
In ancient times, a young warrior rises to protect his people and his kingdom from a tyrannical warlord, fulfilling a prophecy that foretold his destiny as the true Warrior King.
A revisionist take on the legendary outlaws, exploring a deeper, perhaps more contentious, relationship between Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid as they navigate their final days.
A specialized military unit is tasked with an impossible mission behind enemy lines, facing overwhelming odds and internal conflicts as they fight for survival and to complete their objective.
A novelist fed up with the establishment profiting from "Black" entertainment uses a pen name to write a book that propels him into the heart of hypocrisy and the madness he claims to disdain.

Based on the true story of IPS officer Manoj Kumar Sharma, this film chronicles his incredible journey from extreme poverty to achieving his dream of becoming an Indian Police Service officer, despite failing his 12th-grade exams.

titulo: White Fang 2: Myth of the White Wolf
sinopsis: Henry Casey, an old friend of Jack Conroy, takes charge of White Fang while Jack is away. Henry and White Fang embark on an adventure to save a Haida tribe from starvation, guided by the mythical White Wolf.

A young woman who is obsessed with Christmas discovers a magical snow globe that transports her to a perfect Christmas village. However, she soon learns that perfection isn't all it's cracked up to be.

Three British teenage girls go on a rites-of-passage holiday – drinking, clubbing and hooking up, in what should be the best summer of their lives. As they navigate the pressures of conformity and burgeoning sexuality, their friendships are tested.

An aging author struggling with writer's block and loneliness forms an unlikely bond with a young woman who helps him find inspiration and a new perspective on life, leading to one final, poignant story.
In a dystopian future, a man declared dead by the state must fight for his identity and survival, navigating a world where digital records determine one's existence.
A group of students, bored with their university lives, engage in a strange, ritualistic game that blurs the lines between reality and fantasy, leading them on a surreal journey to Tunisia.

A hardworking journalist is assigned to cover a European prince visiting her city during Christmas. As she gets to know him beyond his royal title, an unexpected romance blossoms amidst holiday festivities.

The Thomas family is busy preparing for Christmas when their beloved cat, Mog, causes a series of comical mishaps. Worried she's in trouble, Mog runs away, but Christmas just isn't the same without her.
During a typhoon night, a young gangster, Tai, seeks refuge in a hair salon where he meets Fen, a trainee hairstylist. Despite their different worlds, a quirky romance blossoms between them.
A single mother and her son become the targets of a relentless and psychotic truck driver after a minor road incident escalates into a terrifying game of cat and mouse.

An Oxford student, Edward Bellingham, becomes obsessed with Egyptology and acquires an ancient mummy, Lot No. 249. Strange and terrifying events begin to occur, leading his friends to suspect he has reanimated the mummy for sinister purposes.

titulo: Monster High: Why Do Ghouls Fall in Love?
sinopsis: Draculaura's sweet 1600th birthday is approaching, and she's planning the party of the millennium. But when two vampire boys, Clawd and the new, charming Valentine, vie for her affection, her celebration turns into a monstrous love triangle.

Based on the true story of Ray Santilli and Gary Shoefield, two British entrepreneurs who claimed to have obtained footage of an alien autopsy from the 1947 Roswell incident, and the media frenzy that followed.
An anthology film that brings to life various terrifying internet urban legends and creepypastas, exploring the dark corners of online folklore and their chilling real-world implications.

Two childhood sweethearts, now estranged, are unexpectedly reunited in their hometown for the holidays. As they work together on a Christmas festival, old feelings reignite, but past misunderstandings and new challenges threaten their second chance at love.
A nightclub pianist hitchhiking to Hollywood to join his girlfriend gets entangled with a femme fatale whose manipulative schemes lead him down a dark path of blackmail and murder.

This documentary exposes the dark side of controversial wilderness therapy camps for troubled teens, revealing stories of abuse, neglect, and the lasting trauma inflicted on young people in the name of rehabilitation.
After a heartless firing, Philo plots a revenge plan against her ex-boss, a retail mogul. She skillfully plays the victim, gains the woman's trust and affection, only to orchestrate her downfall.
Three best friends in Mumbai navigate love, ambition, and heartbreak in the age of social media, where online personas often clash with real-life insecurities and desires.
A slice-of-life comedy that follows the interconnected lives of various Parisians as they navigate the ups and downs of relationships, careers, and the everyday absurdities of modern urban life.

In an alternate 1950s America where magic is real and witchcraft is illegal, private detective H. Phillip Lovecraft gets involved in a case involving a glamorous actress who might be a witch, uncovering a conspiracy that goes deeper than he imagined.

A comprehensive documentary charting the history and evolution of the first-person shooter genre in video games, from its origins to its current cultural impact, featuring interviews with developers and industry experts.

A documentary chronicling the Lakota Sioux Nation's century-long fight to reclaim the Black Hills, sacred land that was stolen in violation of treaty agreements, exploring the historical injustices and the ongoing struggle for sovereignty and land rights.

In a polluted near-future, two lesbian parents try to raise their daughter. When their child is kidnapped by a corporation responsible for contaminated fish, they must navigate a bizarre and dangerous world to get her back, involving talking cats and media manipulation.

A remake of the 1971 classic, a former race car driver and decorated war veteran delivering a car from Denver to San Francisco bets he can make the trip in 15 hours. His journey becomes a symbol of rebellion as he evades police across multiple states, guided by a radio DJ.

Cindy, a young woman from a wealthy family in San Pedro, Mexico, flees to Mexico City to escape an unwanted marriage proposal. There, she discovers a new world and new possibilities for herself, challenging her traditional upbringing.

Suddenly left alone during the final stages of her pregnancy, Sara receives an unexpected visit from Linda, her estranged older sister – a needy, immature adult with a broken heart and an empty bank account who offers to move in and help out.

An NTSB investigator discovers a secretive organization of time travelers from a dystopian future who are abducting passengers from doomed airplanes moments before they crash, replacing them with identical bodies to maintain the timeline, as they attempt to repopulate their dying world.

Poppy, a marketing specialist whose life is meticulously planned, is thrown for a loop when she's forced to share her new apartment with a charming but commitment-phobic chef. Their clashing lifestyles lead to unexpected romantic sparks.

In a dystopian future, a fast-food chain serves burgers made from human flesh sourced from criminals. The film follows the grotesque and satirical operations of this establishment, pushing the boundaries of splatter and dark comedy.

Two old friends, Kurt and Mark, reunite for a weekend camping trip in Oregon's Cascade Mountains. As they hike and soak in hot springs, their diverging life paths and unspoken tensions slowly surface, creating a poignant portrait of friendship and change.

A young man arrives in a small, speed-trap town in 1958 California driving a hot-rodded 1934 Ford coupe, seeking to avenge his brother's death at the hands of a sadistic local sheriff who preys on speeders.

A group of small-time crooks plan a heist during a Christmas party, but their scheme quickly goes awry due to incompetence, betrayal, and unexpected complications, leading to a chaotic and humorous series of events.

Scottish comedian Kevin Bridges returns to the stage for his highly anticipated stand-up special, 'The Overdue Catch-Up.' Filmed live, he delivers his trademark observational humor on topics ranging from everyday life to global events.

Based on Honoré de Balzac's novel, this period drama follows Bette, a poor and embittered spinster in 19th-century Paris, who schemes to ruin the lives of her wealthy relatives after years of perceived slights and mistreatment.

In a remote, snow-covered landscape, a desperate group of individuals find their lives intertwining as they struggle for survival against the harsh elements and a dangerous, unseen threat lurking in the wilderness.

In 18th-century Denmark, Captain Ludvig Kahlen sets out to conquer the harsh, uninhabitable Jutland heath with a seemingly impossible goal: to build a colony in the name of the King. However, he faces an unforgiving adversary in the local landowner.

Ricky Gervais returns to Netflix with his provocative new stand-up special, 'Armageddon.' True to form, Gervais tackles controversial topics and challenges societal norms with his signature dark humor and sharp wit.

A group of six diverse friends navigate the complexities of life, love, and careers in a bustling metropolis. Their intertwined stories explore modern relationships and the challenges of finding connection in an urban landscape.

A documentary exploring the life, work, and impact of Tom Wolfe, the pioneering journalist and author known for his flamboyant style and incisive critiques of American culture. The film delves into his 'New Journalism' approach and his iconic books.

Four friends from a small village in Punjab share a common dream: to go to England. Their journey involves an illegal immigration technique called 'Dunki Flight,' leading them through a perilous and life-changing adventure.

A dark comedy about a down-on-his-luck man who, after a series of bizarre misfortunes, finds himself in a surreal and dangerous situation involving a valuable, dismembered head and a cast of eccentric characters.

A fledgling comedian, desperate for success, makes a Faustian bargain with a mysterious entity to become hilarious. However, he soon discovers the dark and unsettling price of his newfound comedic talent.

A man, on the brink of a nervous breakdown, impulsively decides to hike a remote New Zealand track. As he ventures deeper into the wilderness, paranoia sets in, and he becomes convinced he is being stalked, blurring the lines between reality and his fragile mental state.

Fernandinho, a timid ex-soccer player turned podcast host, is shocked to discover that his inconvenient brother-in-law, Gregório, is not only a lazy freeloader but also a vampire with world-domination plans.

titulo: Monster High: Scaris City of Frights
sinopsis: Clawdeen Wolf gets the chance to apprentice for the legendary fashion designer Madame Ghostier in Scaris, France. She and her ghoulfriends pack their bags and head to the City of Frights, but soon discover that not everything is as glamorous as it seems.

A group of friends on a secluded getaway find themselves hunted by a malevolent force that was awakened by their presence. As they fight for survival, they uncover the dark history of the place and the entity that haunts it.

Two aspiring roadmen, Riko and Kane, try to make a name for themselves in the London underworld. However, their attempts to get rich quick and earn respect are hilariously inept, leading to a series of disastrous and comedic encounters.

A documentary exploring the Gerson Therapy, a controversial alternative cancer treatment developed by Dr. Max Gerson. The film presents testimonials from patients and practitioners, advocating for its efficacy against various diseases.

Two estranged brothers, a grumpy truck driver and his more optimistic sibling, are forced to work together to deliver Christmas gifts and a festive spirit to the remote, struggling town of Willow Creek, Alaska.

Two ex-lovers, Bill and Willa, find themselves snowed in at a regional airport overnight. Forced to confront their past, they reminisce, argue, and explore what might have been, leading to unexpected revelations and a possible rekindling.

Norma, a woman leading an ordinary life, decides to break free from societal expectations and embark on a journey of self-discovery after a life-altering event. She challenges conventions and redefines her own happiness.

After an amazing first date, Bea and Ben's fiery attraction turns ice cold — until they find themselves unexpectedly reunited at a destination wedding in Australia. So they do what any two mature adults would do: pretend to be a couple.
A mysterious mastermind and his team execute a massive bank heist. As the police try to uncover his identity and motives, a thrilling cat-and-mouse game ensues, revealing a larger conspiracy.

A photographer, cynical about Christmas, is assigned to cover a small town's famous holiday festival. There, she meets a charming local who helps her rediscover the magic of the season and the importance of community.

A talented but overlooked fashion designer gets a chance to make her mark when she's hired by a demanding fashion mogul. She must navigate the cutthroat industry, personal rivalries, and find her own voice to achieve her dreams.

The true story of the inseparable Von Erich brothers, who made history in the intensely competitive world of professional wrestling in the early 1980s. Through tragedy and triumph, they seek ring immortality under the shadow of their domineering father and coach.

Mary Ann, a single mother, adopts a baby girl at Christmas. As she prepares for the holiday, a series of heartwarming events and unexpected connections bring her and her new daughter closer to the true meaning of family and faith.

titulo: Curry & Cyanide: The Jolly Joseph Case
sinopsis: This true crime documentary investigates the chilling case of Jolly Joseph, a woman in Kerala, India, accused of murdering six family members over 14 years by poisoning them with cyanide-laced food and drink.
A young woman moves into a state-of-the-art smart home, only to discover that its advanced AI system has a sinister agenda and begins to terrorize her, turning her dream home into a high-tech prison.

titulo: Rebel Moon - Part One: A Child of Fire
sinopsis: When a peaceful colony on the edge of a galaxy finds itself threatened by the armies of a tyrannical ruling force, Kora, a mysterious stranger living among the villagers, becomes their best hope for survival.

A young ex-con, recently released from prison, risks his newfound freedom to track down the estranged daughter of a fellow inmate at the request of his dying mentor, uncovering dangerous secrets along the way.

Struggling to find his place at Oxford University, student Oliver Quick finds himself drawn into the world of the charming and aristocratic Felix Catton, who invites him to Saltburn, his eccentric family's sprawling estate, for a summer never to be forgotten.

A hapless family man finds his life turned upside down when millions of strangers suddenly start seeing him in their dreams. When his nighttime appearances take a nightmarish turn, Paul Matthews is forced to navigate his newfound stardom.

titulo: Juice: How Electricity Explains The World
sinopsis: A documentary that explores the profound and often overlooked impact of electricity on the modern world, from powering our cities and technologies to shaping global economies and inequalities.

The Bratz girls buy a seemingly ordinary lamp at a bazaar, only to discover it houses a teenage genie named Katia. To free Katia from the lamp forever, they must grant her three wishes, leading to magical adventures and a trip to London.

A sexually charged and surreal art film exploring themes of desire, voyeurism, and the human body through a series of loosely connected, often explicit, vignettes. (Note: This is an adult film, sinopsis kept general).

Gannu, an alcoholic in a small town, makes a vow to stay sober until the birth of his child to win back his wife's affection and set a good example. His personal struggle becomes a public spectacle, challenging local norms and his own resolve.

A famous Spanish film director, Miguel Garay, retired years ago after the mysterious disappearance of his lead actor and close friend, Julio Arenas, during the filming of a movie. Decades later, a TV show revives interest in the case, prompting Miguel to revisit his past and the unfinished film.

A desperate woman, haunted by past trauma and battling addiction, finds herself in a fight for survival when she becomes entangled with dangerous criminals in a gritty underworld. She must confront her demons to make it through another day.

A documentary delving into the shocking true story of Paolo Macchiarini, a charismatic surgeon who gained international fame for his supposed breakthroughs in regenerative medicine, only for his web of deceit and failed experiments to be exposed.

When a new department store Santa claims to be the real Kris Kringle, a series of terrifying and unexplainable events begin to plague the store and its employees, turning holiday cheer into yuletide fear.

Kaska and Patryk's turbulent love story continues. When they suspect each other of infidelity, their already fiery relationship explodes into a series of comical misunderstandings and schemes as they try to outwit one another.

titulo: Christmas with The Chosen: Holy Night
sinopsis: A special Christmas presentation featuring an episode of 'The Chosen' that tells the story of Jesus' birth, combined with musical performances from contemporary Christian artists, celebrating the meaning of the holiday.

A young couple, deeply in love, faces an unimaginable crisis when their newborn child is diagnosed with a rare and life-threatening condition. Their faith, relationship, and strength are tested as they fight for their baby's survival.
Indian comedian Vir Das returns with a new stand-up special, reflecting on his global experiences, cultural identity, and the absurdities of modern life, all filmed during his world tour.

A free-spirited young woman who believes in fate and magic meets a pragmatic and somewhat cynical man. Their chance encounter leads them on a whimsical and romantic journey, challenging their perspectives on love and life.

Lucy, a former child actor, seeks enlightenment at a silent retreat led by her spiritual guru. However, her disruptive presence and unresolved issues with her stunt-performer daughter create chaos and confrontation.

Cliff Spab, a disaffected teenager, along with his friend Joe, are taken hostage in a convenience store by terrorists. The ensuing 36-day siege is televised, turning Cliff into an unwilling media sensation known for his catchphrase 'So Fucking What?'

An ex-convict trying to go straight in San Francisco is framed for a murder he didn't commit by his vengeful brother and a relentless police detective. He must clear his name while protecting his wife and daughter.

In the drought-stricken Brazilian Sertão of the 1940s, a poor cowhand named Manuel kills his tyrannical boss and flees with his wife, Rosa. They become entangled with two messianic figures: a self-proclaimed saint and a ruthless bandit leader, embodying religious fanaticism and violent rebellion.

In 1930s Paris, Madeleine, a pretty, young, and penniless actress, is accused of murdering a famous producer. Helped by her best friend Pauline, a young unemployed lawyer, she is acquitted on the grounds of self-defense. A new life of fame and success begins, until the truth comes out.

A talented quilt maker is hired by a charming but skeptical historian to create a historically accurate Christmas quilt for a town festival. As they work together, they uncover local history and find an unexpected romantic connection.
After discovering that a teacher at South Park Elementary is moonlighting with an OnlyFans page, Randy is compelled to take a closer look at the seedy underbelly of the world of online influencers.

A candid and insightful documentary where legendary comedian, actor, and filmmaker Albert Brooks sits down with his lifelong friend Rob Reiner to discuss his career, his unique comedic voice, and his impact on comedy.

Having failed to defeat Aquaman the first time, Black Manta, still driven by the need to avenge his father's death, will stop at nothing to take Aquaman down once and for all. This time Black Manta is more formidable than ever before, wielding the power of the mythical Black Trident, which unleashes an ancient and malevolent force.

The story of Polly Franklin, a young woman who becomes infamous as John Dillinger's 'Lady in Red.' The film follows her journey from a small town to the Chicago underworld, her relationship with Dillinger, and the events leading to his death.

Years after escaping a terrifying evil, Rini and her younger siblings live in a rundown apartment building. They believe they are safe, but the malevolent entity they thought they left behind returns, seeking to claim one of them for a sinister purpose.

A towering and fearless love story chronicling the lifelong relationship between cultural icon Leonard Bernstein and Felicia Montealegre Cohn Bernstein. A love letter to life and art, Maestro at its core is an emotionally epic portrayal of family and love.

A group of strangers from different walks of life connect through an online chat forum. As their virtual relationships deepen, they decide to meet in person, leading to unexpected friendships, romances, and revelations.

In a small, isolated town, a sudden and inexplicable plague of aggressive flies descends upon the residents, causing panic and chaos. A group of survivors must band together to understand the phenomenon and fight for their lives.

In 1937 Czechoslovakia, on the eve of World War II, a young woman working in a shoe factory discovers the intersex body of a stillborn child. This discovery throws her into a moral and existential crisis, forcing her to confront the era's rigid societal norms and her own identity.

During the Seminole Wars in 1840s Florida, U.S. Army Captain Quincy Wyatt leads a mission to destroy a fort used by gun-runners. After the successful raid, he and his men must make a perilous journey back through the Everglades, pursued by vengeful Seminole warriors.

A cynical businesswoman inherits her estranged grandfather's Christmas-themed shop in a small, festive town. She plans to sell it quickly but finds herself charmed by the town's holiday spirit and a handsome local, Mr. Christmas himself.

Nicky and Gabriel, a loving couple, are in the midst of a contentious divorce. The film explores their battle for custody of their eight-year-old son, Owen, forcing them to confront their past, their present, and what it means to be a family.

A woman is suspected of her husband's murder, and their blind son faces a moral dilemma as the main witness. The trial unearths their complex and troubled relationship, questioning truth and perception.
A young Jewish cantor defies his strict father and traditions to pursue his dream of becoming a popular music singer. His journey is one of conflict between heritage, ambition, and love.

Trevor Noah returns to Netflix with a new stand-up special, sharing his hilarious experiences from his recent travels around the world, offering his unique perspective on global cultures and current events.

Bonnie, a personal shopper, is hired by a pragmatic, workaholic widower to find the perfect gifts for his children. As she helps him reconnect with his family and the holiday spirit, an unexpected romance blossoms.

Clyde Beatty travels to the lost city of Joba in darkest Africa to rescue the kidnapped Goddess of Joba, battling fierce animals, treacherous natives, and winged warriors in this classic 15-chapter serial.

A small town's beloved annual Christmas pageant is in jeopardy due to budget cuts. A group of determined locals, led by a passionate young woman, bands together to save the tradition, rediscovering the true meaning of Christmas along the way.

titulo: The Hunger Games: The Ballad of Songbirds & Snakes
sinopsis: Years before he would become the tyrannical President of Panem, 18-year-old Coriolanus Snow is the last hope for his fading lineage. He is assigned to mentor Lucy Gray Baird, the girl tribute from impoverished District 12, in the 10th Hunger Games.

After a Black Friday riot ends in tragedy, a mysterious Thanksgiving-inspired killer terrorizes Plymouth, Massachusetts – the birthplace of the holiday. One by one, the residents become victims as the killer carves out a bloody holiday feast.

A grieving father enacts his long-awaited revenge against a ruthless gang on Christmas Eve. He witnesses his young son die when caught in a gang's crossfire. While recovering from a wound that costs him his voice, he makes vengeance his life's mission.

During World War II, a Black soldier faces racial prejudice from his white comrades while on a dangerous reconnaissance mission on a Japanese-held island in the South Pacific. The film explores the psychological toll of racism and combat.

titulo: Hell on Earth: The Fall of Syria and the Rise of ISIS
sinopsis: A harrowing documentary that examines the Syrian Civil War and the subsequent rise of the Islamic State (ISIS). Through firsthand accounts and graphic footage, it depicts the devastating human cost of the conflict and the complex geopolitical forces at play.

A mother is trapped in a self-driving car by an unknown entity who forces her to complete a series of increasingly dangerous tasks. If she refuses, the mysterious voice threatens to harm her daughter.

Penelope, a theater director, is skeptical about Christmas but finds herself directing her town's annual Christmas pageant. When the charming but mysterious man playing Santa seems to possess real magic, she starts to question her beliefs.

Two rival relationship advice podcasters, who secretly despise each other, are forced to collaborate on a new show. As they navigate their professional animosity, they discover an unexpected romantic chemistry.

Four lazy, aimless friends in Delhi dream of getting rich quick. They enlist the help of Choocha, who has the ability to dream lottery-winning numbers, and get entangled with a formidable local gangster, Bholi Punjaban.

Retired British spy Harry Palmer is lured back into the world of espionage when he's tasked with a dangerous mission in post-Soviet Russia involving stolen plutonium and a North Korean connection, leading him on a perilous journey to Beijing.

A journalist is sent to cover the grand reopening of a historic ice palace hotel. There, she clashes with the charming but stubborn owner, but as they work together to save the hotel's legacy, a warm romance blossoms in the frosty setting.

Lara, a devout woman struggling with mental illness, is convinced she is possessed by a demon. Her husband, desperate to save her, allows a charlatan exorcist into their home, leading to a terrifying and tragic ordeal.

When Santa's workshop is in trouble, a young, determined elf named Glisten teams up with a cynical reindeer to embark on a magical adventure to save Christmas, learning about friendship and the spirit of giving along the way.

Cecilia, a bright young college student, takes on a Christmas internship at a major company. She unexpectedly finds herself working closely with the charming but work-obsessed CEO, teaching him about the holiday spirit and finding romance.

Set in the summer of 1957, with Enzo Ferrari's auto empire in crisis, the ex-racer turned entrepreneur pushes himself and his drivers to the edge as they launch into the Mille Miglia, a treacherous 1,000-mile race across Italy.
Ethan Hunt and his IMF team continue their most dangerous mission yet, facing an all-powerful AI enemy known as the Entity, with the fate of the world and their own lives hanging in the balance.
elenco: Tom Cruise, Hayley Atwell, Ving Rhames, Simon Pegg, Esai Morales, Vanessa Kirby, Pom Klementieff, Henry Czerny.

sinopsis: A live-action adaptation of the immensely popular sandbox video game, bringing the blocky world and its creative possibilities to life on the big screen in a new adventure.
elenco: Jack Black, Jason Momoa, Danielle Brooks, Emma Myers, Sebastian Eugene Hansen, Jennifer Coolidge, Kate McKinnon, Jemaine Clement.

sinopsis: In 1932, identical twins and World War I veterans Elijah 'Smoke' and Elias 'Stack' Moore return to Clarksdale, Mississippi, after years of working for the Chicago mob. Using stolen money, they buy a lumberyard to open a blues club catering to the local Black community. However, their bid for redemption is threatened by a supernatural presence lurking in the shadows, sparking a struggle between their dark past and evil forces that will test their familial ties and their faith.
A live-action adaptation of Disney's animated classic. A lonely Hawaiian girl named Lilo adopts a small, ugly 'dog' she names Stitch, who turns out to be a mischievous alien experiment.

Two estranged siblings partner on a global heist to find the mythological Fountain of Youth. They must use their knowledge of history to follow clues on an epic adventure that could lead to immortality.
Sam Wilson, now Captain America, grapples with new threats and the responsibilities of his mantle in a world that is rapidly changing.

A new group of individuals must find a way to escape Death's design after they cheat their fate. This installment is expected to delve into the family history of some characters connected to the deadly premonitions.
A young man's desperate search for his missing daughter leads him to a remote and mysterious mountain, where he uncovers dark secrets and confronts terrifying forces.

Plot details are kept under wraps, but it will unite characters from different generations of the Karate Kid franchise, likely involving a new young protagonist learning martial arts from legendary mentors.
An 'expendable' employee on a human expedition sent to colonize an ice world Niflheim, refuses to let his clone replacement, Mickey 18, take his place after a dangerous mission.
The film follows a grieving man who, after the mysterious death of his wife, begins to suspect that she may not be entirely gone and that a malevolent force is at play.
A star P.I. is hired to find a missing girl and gets caught up in a dangerous conspiracy involving a valuable artifact and powerful figures.
A group of supervillains and anti-heroes are recruited by the government to embark on dangerous missions, offering them a chance at redemption... or a path to further chaos.
A man, after his beloved grandmother passes away, decides to open a restaurant staffed by grandmothers to honor her memory and cooking, leading to heartwarming and comedic results.
Set in 1988, Shadyside High's prom season is in full swing, but when a new girl with a mysterious past becomes a prom queen contender, a series of terrifying events begin to unfold.

A group of friends returns to a remote mountain lodge where two of their group disappeared a year prior. Soon, they find themselves hunted by a malevolent force, and their choices determine who survives the night. Based on the popular video game.
Guillermo del Toro's adaptation of Mary Shelley's classic novel, exploring the themes of creation, monstrosity, and humanity through the story of Victor Frankenstein and his tragic creation.
A psychological thriller where a woman's seemingly perfect life unravels after she becomes entangled with a mysterious and dangerous individual, leading to a deadly game of cat and mouse.

A revisionist take on the Cinderella story, focusing on one of the 'ugly' stepsisters, Elvira, as she navigates societal pressures, complex family dynamics, and her own journey of self-discovery beyond the shadow of her famous stepsister.
The film follows the daily struggles and quiet dignity of a blue-collar worker facing economic hardship and trying to provide for his family in a rapidly changing world.
An intense and gritty portrayal of soldiers on the front lines, focusing on the psychological toll and brutal realities of combat. Specific plot details are under wraps.
A live-action reimagining of the classic Disney animated film, telling the story of a princess who escapes her evil stepmother, the Queen, and finds refuge with seven dwarfs in a forest.
After a drug deal gone wrong, a bruised detective must fight his way through a criminal underworld to rescue a politician's estranged son, while unraveling a deep web of corruption and conspiracy.

Christian Wolff, the brilliant but deadly freelance accountant, returns for another high-stakes case that will likely involve uncooking books for dangerous clients and dispensing his own brand of justice.
A tense spy thriller with plot details kept confidential, expected to involve covert operations, espionage, and high-stakes international intrigue.
A bank executive with a rare genetic condition that prevents him from feeling pain is taken hostage by a dangerous criminal, leading to a violent and unpredictable confrontation.
A professional matchmaker in New York gets entangled with a wealthy man but still harbors feelings for her ex-boyfriend, a broke actor-waiter, leading to a complex romantic triangle.

The origin story of Marvel's first family: Reed Richards, Sue Storm, Johnny Storm, and Ben Grimm, who gain extraordinary abilities after a fateful mission to space, becoming Mr. Fantastic, Invisible Woman, Human Torch, and The Thing.
Vikram Rudraraju from the Homicide Intervention Team (HIT) takes on another challenging and perplexing murder mystery that pushes his investigative skills to the limit.
An aging rodeo champion contemplates one final ride, reflecting on his past glories, sacrifices, and the changing world of rodeo, while dealing with personal and health challenges.
A poignant story about a young astronomer who, while searching for a new celestial body, embarks on a journey of self-discovery and connection after a personal loss.
A tense thriller centered around a high-stakes meeting or appointment that holds life-altering consequences for the individuals involved, with secrets and dangers lurking.

Stephanie Smothers and Emily Nelson head to the beautiful island of Capri, Italy, for Emily’s lavish wedding to a wealthy Italian businessman. Along with the glamorous guests, murder and betrayal swirl through the proceedings, turning a picturesque wedding into a dangerous affair.
A deep-sea exploration team uncovers a mysterious anomaly at the bottom of the ocean, leading them to a terrifying discovery that threatens not only their lives but potentially the world.
A faith-based animated film that tells the story of Jesus Christ, focusing on his teachings, miracles, and the profound impact he had on humanity, inspired by a short story by Charles Dickens.

A father and his teenage daughter accidentally hit a unicorn while driving. The situation becomes more complicated and bizarre as they try to deal with the magical creature and the consequences of their actions.

The film explores the complex legal and moral issues surrounding a diplomatic territory or individual operating outside the jurisdiction of the host country, leading to a high-stakes international incident.
An action-packed drama centered around a powerful figure named Sikandar, whose life is filled with conflict, ambition, and a fight for dominance in a challenging environment.
An estranged couple with a bounty on their heads must go on the run with their son to avoid their former employer, a clandestine unit of special operatives.

Daniella and Amelia, two artists with different styles, are both chosen to curate an art gallery's Christmas Eve charity event. As they work together, they discover that their clashing styles and personalities hide a deeper connection.

titulo: I Do Not Care If We Go Down in History as Barbarians
sinopsis: A young theatre director is preparing to stage a reenactment of a historical event, the 1941 Odessa Massacre, in which Romanian troops slaughtered tens of thousands of Ukrainian Jews. Her efforts are met with resistance from local officials and actors alike, who question the relevance and appropriateness of revisiting such a dark chapter in their nation's past.

A legendary 1964 concert film featuring performances by The Rolling Stones, James Brown, The Beach Boys, Chuck Berry, Marvin Gaye, Smokey Robinson & The Miracles, The Supremes, and many more. Filmed at the Santa Monica Civic Auditorium.

In 1970s England, three blue-collar friends spend their days joking, drinking, fighting and chasing girls. Freddie wants to leave their working-class world but cool, charismatic Bruce and lovable loser Snork are happy with life the way it is. When Freddie gets a new job as a door-to-door salesman, he's pitted against his old friends and his new boss's daughter.

titulo: The Bad Guys: A Very Bad Holiday
sinopsis: To keep their annual Christmas Day heist on track, Mr. Wolf and his crew of animal outlaws will have to restore the city's holiday spirit in a hurry when Christmas is unexpectedly canceled.

titulo: Meet Me at the Christmas Train Parade
sinopsis: A single mother and her young son are charmed by a local station agent during the town's annual Christmas train parade. As they spend more time together, they discover the magic of Christmas and the possibility of new love.
A pregnant single mother, with two children in foster care, embraces her Bay Area community as she fights to reclaim her family.
A group of finishing school students are terrorized by a killer in a Santa Claus suit during their Christmas break.

The story of Albert C. Barnes, who amassed a fortune in pharmaceuticals and used it to acquire a stunning collection of post-Impressionist art, which he housed in a foundation in a Philadelphia suburb. After his death, a powerful group of Philadelphia insiders fought to move the collection to a new museum downtown, against Barnes's explicit wishes.

A young woman discovers that she is the focus of an evil nazi experiment involving selective breeding and summoned elves, an attempt to create a race of supermen. She and two of her friends are trapped in a department store with an elf, and only Dan Haggerty, as the renegade Santa Claus, can save them.

A travel writer is assigned to cover a small town's Christmas festivities. While there, she meets a charming local who helps her rediscover the holiday spirit and concocts a plan to help her ex-boyfriend propose, only to realize her own feelings might be changing.
A woman returns to her hometown for her high school reunion, only to find herself entangled in a dangerous mystery when old secrets and rivalries resurface, and a former classmate turns up dead.
Carley sets out to conquer her list of abandoned resolutions from last year. Aided by her coworker, she unexpectedly finds love and the confidence to chase her dreams.
In postwar Japan, a new terror rises. Will the devastated people be able to fight back... or even survive?

In the bustling metropolis, a renegade cop and his unlikely partner must navigate a web of corruption and conspiracy to stop a ruthless criminal organization from executing a devastating city-wide attack.

Dolores Quantero, a descendant of the legendary Zorro-like hero Don Quixote (Don Q), finds herself targeted by a shadowy syndicate trying to steal her family's valuable land grant. She must use her wits and inherited fighting skills to unmask the villains and protect her legacy.
A U.S. Marine officer and his sergeant investigate sabotage at a remote island airbase, suspecting a mysterious mastermind known as 'The Tiger Shark' who is stealing a new aircraft guidance system.

Ace federal agent Jerry Blake (Operator 99) takes on a sophisticated counterfeiting ring led by the elusive Jim Belmont. Blake must unravel Belmont's intricate schemes and bring him to justice before the nation's economy is crippled.

When Santa Claus loses his Christmas spirit, a determined group of ordinary people, led by a cynical photographer, must band together to help him rediscover the magic of the holiday and save Christmas for everyone.

Inspired by Mickey Guyton's song, four disparate people find themselves stranded in a local diner on Christmas Eve when a snowstorm hits. As they share their stories, they find hope, healing, and the true meaning of Christmas.

A successful but commitment-phobic author known for her dating advice books returns to her hometown for Christmas. There, she encounters her high school sweetheart, a charming local who challenges her views on love and relationships, forcing her to confront her own fears about opening her heart.

A team of paranormal investigators sets out to film a documentary about a notoriously haunted location. As they delve deeper into the site's dark history, they uncover a malevolent presence that begins to toy with their perceptions of reality, turning their project into a fight for survival.

An undocumented Filipina immigrant lands a job as a caretaker for a wealthy, terminally ill old man. As she settles into her new role, she uncovers a sinister secret within the household, one that threatens not only her livelihood but also her life and that of her young daughter.

Two former childhood friends, now competitive adults, are roped into a series of holiday-themed dares by their respective families. As they navigate the increasingly outrageous challenges, they rediscover their connection and the true spirit of Christmas.

A rescue mission to a remote part of Loch Ness takes a terrifying turn when the team encounters not only the legendary monster but also a hidden, hostile ecosystem. They must fight for survival against prehistoric creatures and the harsh environment.

A stenographer in a small Southern town, content with his quiet life, witnesses a heinous crime. This event awakens a dormant, violent side of him, leading him down a dark path of vigilante justice as he seeks to protect the innocent and punish the guilty.

titulo: Chicken Run: Dawn of the Nugget
sinopsis: Having pulled off a death-defying escape from Tweedy's farm, Ginger has finally found her dream – a peaceful island sanctuary for the whole flock, far from the dangers of the human world. When she and Rocky hatch a little girl called Molly, Ginger’s happy ending seems complete. But back on the mainland the whole of chicken-kind faces a new and terrible threat.

In 1990s Los Angeles, a man struggling with writer's block after a breakup finds himself confronting a new, more immediate crisis: a zombie apocalypse. He must navigate the chaos with his ex-girlfriend and best friend, all while trying to finish his novel.

A group of five estranged childhood friends reunites after years apart to fulfill a pact made long ago. As they embark on their shared mission, they confront past grievances, rekindle old bonds, and discover that some promises are harder to keep than others, especially when a hidden danger emerges.

Morán, a bank employee in Buenos Aires, devises a plan to liberate himself and his colleague Román from the drudgery of corporate life: Morán will steal enough money for them both to never work again, then confess and serve prison time while Román hides the cash. Soon, under pressure from an internal investigation, Román is driven to a remote hideaway to protect their secret.

To celebrate their engagement, Thea takes Jashan home to rural Norway to spend Christmas with her family. But Jashan’s Indian roots and Thea’s family’s Norwegian traditions clash in a chaotic and heartwarming holiday.

After the sudden death of her husband, Nawal, a young Jordanian mother, finds herself facing a dire situation. According to local inheritance laws, without a male heir, her late husband's family is entitled to a significant portion of their home and her belongings. Desperate to protect her daughter and their future, Nawal must navigate a patriarchal system and consider drastic measures.

A group of thrill-seeking friends stumbles upon a hidden stash of money linked to dangerous criminals. Their find quickly turns into a fight for survival as they are hunted by those who want the cash back, forcing them to use their wits and courage to escape.

In a modern interpretation of the classic tale, Dracula's ancient curse is reawakened, unleashing a new reign of terror upon an unsuspecting world. A diverse group of individuals must band together to confront the legendary vampire and his insatiable thirst for blood before humanity is doomed.

Stranded in the Saudi desert after a clandestine party, a young woman named Sarah must race against time and treacherous terrain to make it home before her strict father discovers her absence. Her journey becomes a desperate fight for survival against the elements and her own fears.

The film follows the journey of Clémence and her cat, Rroû, as they leave Paris for the countryside. While Clémence thrives in this new environment, Rroû discovers the wild life and befriends Câline, a white kitten. Their parallel adventures explore themes of freedom, nature, and the unique bond between humans and animals.

A devout and wealthy Nigerian man, recently retired, grapples with a profound loss of faith after a personal tragedy. He hires a young, optimistic house manager whose presence challenges his cynicism and gradually helps him rediscover hope, purpose, and the possibility of healing.

Dan Morgan is a devoted husband, father of three, and successful car salesman. But decades ago, he was an elite government assassin tasked with eliminating the world's deadliest threats. When his past catches up to him, Dan packs his unsuspecting wife and kids into their minivan and takes them on an impromptu cross-country road trip to Las Vegas, all while trying to evade his former enemies.

A seemingly innocuous yule log video takes a dark and surreal turn as strange events unfold within the static frame of a crackling fireplace. What begins as a cozy holiday backdrop slowly reveals a hidden narrative of unsettling occurrences and mysterious figures, blurring the line between festive tradition and psychological horror.

A pragmatic app developer returns to her hometown to help save her family's traditional candle-making business, which is struggling in the modern market. While there, she clashes with, and then falls for, a charming local artisan who reminds her of the importance of heritage, community, and the magic of Christmas.

Gu Wentong, a middle-aged food critic in Beijing, reconnects with his estranged father after decades of separation. As he navigates this complex relationship, he also forms a bond with a younger photographer. The film explores themes of family, memory, and the search for connection in a rapidly changing urban landscape.

When teenage Priscilla Beaulieu meets Elvis Presley at a party, the man who is already a meteoric rock-and-roll superstar becomes someone entirely unexpected in private moments: a thrilling crush, an ally in loneliness, a vulnerable best friend. Through Priscilla’s eyes, Sofia Coppola tells the unseen side of a great American myth in Elvis and Priscilla's long courtship and turbulent marriage.

Two estranged brothers, raised in different worlds, are reunited as adults over one fateful summer. When desperate circumstances force them to strike a deal with a dangerous Boston crime syndicate, a young woman finds herself caught in the middle. Sacrifices must be made, and bonds between brothers, friends, and a father and his sons are put to the test.

A group of medical students experimenting with a powerful hallucinogen unleashes a pair of sexually sadistic serial killers from their subconscious. As reality blurs and the body count rises, they must confront the monsters they've manifested before they become the next victims.

A documentary following a diverse group of individuals who make the courageous decision to volunteer for military service during a time of conflict. The film explores their motivations, training, and the profound impact of war on their lives and the lives of their families.

A former boxing champion, disgraced and struggling, is given a chance at redemption when he's tasked with training a group of underprivileged youths from a poor mountainous region. Through grit, determination, and unlikely bonds, they aim to defy the odds and achieve the impossible in the ring.

The adult siblings of the Fitzgerald family prepare for their estranged father to join them for Christmas for the first time in twenty years, leading to a mix of old resentments and new understandings.
A mother nurses her sick daughter, who is afflicted with a mysterious ailment. Their isolated existence is threatened when uninvited guests arrive during a Christmas blizzard.

After her husband's devastating accident, a grieving widow moves to a remote Scottish island where she uncovers a mysterious portrait that seems to hold a dark secret about its subject and her own past.

A charming but down-on-his-luck widower and his two children inherit a struggling vineyard. To save it, he must team up with a determined local winemaker who initially clashes with his city ways, leading to unexpected romance amidst the holiday season.

titulo: Happiness Is a Warm Blanket, Charlie Brown
sinopsis: Linus is pushed to his limits when his grandmother attempts to separate him from his beloved security blanket before her upcoming visit. The Peanuts gang tries to help Linus cope, with varying degrees of success.
A young war widow is torn between a safe, reliable suitor and a charming, somewhat irresponsible stranger she meets while working as a comparison shopper during the Christmas season.

A documentary featuring Michael Ruppert, a former LAPD officer turned investigative journalist, who details his apocalyptic vision of the future, predicting the collapse of industrial civilization due to resource depletion and economic instability.

A woman's life unravels after she discovers a mysterious, sentient hole in her apartment that begins to satisfy her deepest, unspoken desires, leading her down a path of surreal and disturbing transformation.

An idealistic young teacher decides to investigate a series of thefts at her new school. Her well-intentioned methods soon spiral out of control, creating an atmosphere of mistrust and paranoia among students, parents, and colleagues.

A food and wine critic, known for her harsh reviews, reluctantly visits a small-town winery for a Christmas festival. She clashes with the charming but stubborn owner, only to discover that their initial animosity might be hiding a deeper connection and a shared passion for perfection.

A discontented young man discovers he can travel back in time to his middle school days. He decides to use this ability to save his former girlfriend from being murdered by a notorious gang, forcing him to relive his troubled past and confront its dangers.
Experience the breathtaking Eras Tour, a cinematic journey through Taylor Swift's iconic musical eras. This concert film captures the magic, energy, and spectacle of her record-breaking global tour.

A Chinese martial artist marries a Japanese woman, leading to a series of misunderstandings and friendly duels as he's challenged by her Japanese martial arts masters, each showcasing different styles, to prove the superiority of Chinese Kung Fu.

A talented but overlooked culinary school instructor gets a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to compete in a prestigious Christmas cooking competition. She must navigate professional rivalries and a budding romance with a charming food critic to achieve her dreams.

In the 1990s Netherlands, a young man with a passion for piano finds himself drawn into the burgeoning, intense world of gabber music and hardcore techno, navigating friendships, ambitions, and the darker sides of the subculture.

A woman finds herself reliving the same Hanukkah night over and over again. To break the loop, she must figure out what she needs to learn or change, with the help of a charming new acquaintance she keeps meeting for the 'first' time.

After a man loses his memory in a freak accident, he uses an eight-and-a-half million pound settlement to obsessively and meticulously reconstruct and re-enact vague, fragmented memories from his past, hoping to find meaning and identity.

In 1970s North Madras, a young man from the Sarpatta boxing clan gets an opportunity to reclaim his clan's lost glory and his own self-respect by fighting a formidable rival from the Idiyappan clan, amidst political and personal turmoil.
After a botched robbery, three violent criminals take a man, a woman, and a sick child hostage in their car, leading to a tense and brutal journey as they try to evade the police.
A criminologist battles a mysterious villain known as Captain Mephisto, who seeks a powerful transformative ray on a remote island, in this action-packed Republic Pictures serial.

A man is tasked with taking his sister-in-law's body back to their countryside hometown after a tragic accident in Saigon. Along the way, he begins a journey to find his long-lost older brother, leading to mystical encounters and reflections on faith, loss, and the meaning of life.
A disillusioned young man working a dead-end job at a Christian youth center attempts to find meaning and connection in his life, leading to a series of awkward and darkly comedic encounters.

A documentary exploring the historical rivalry and eventual convergence of traditional hand-drawn animation (pencils) and computer-generated imagery (pixels) in the animation industry, featuring insights from legendary artists and innovators.
A gripping dramatization of the 2008 Mumbai terrorist attacks, focusing on the events at the Taj Mahal Palace Hotel and the bravery of the victims and security forces during the siege.

A family of ducks, the Mallards, are in a bit of a rut. While dad Mack is content to keep his family safe paddling around their New England pond forever, mom Pam is eager to shake things up and show their kids the whole wide world. After a migrating duck family alights on their pond with thrilling tales of faraway places, Pam persuades Mack to embark on a family vacation, south for the winter to Jamaica.

The film adaptation of the classic British sitcom. Harold Steptoe, the eternally frustrated son in a rag-and-bone business, finally gets married, only to have his curmudgeonly father, Albert, sabotage his honeymoon and his hopes for a new life.

When her daughter is abducted during a family camping trip in Yellowstone National Park, a frantic mother must team up with a local tracker to navigate the treacherous wilderness and outwit the kidnappers before it's too late.

A perpetually cautious woman who always says 'no' to new experiences is challenged by her friends to say 'yes' to everything for a week leading up to Christmas. This new philosophy leads her on a series of festive adventures and an unexpected romance.

Based on Viking mythology, a forgotten king, Eirick, must rise above his past and rally an army to battle the thunder god Thor, who is on a destructive path to gather ancient relics and conquer the world.

Three interconnected stories unfold on Christmas Eve on Cherry Lane: a young couple preparing for their first child, an empty-nester couple navigating new holiday traditions, and a family grappling with a significant life change, all discovering the true meaning of Christmas.

A big-city real estate executive returns to her hometown for Christmas to close a deal on a local ranch. She unexpectedly falls for the ruggedly handsome cowboy owner who is determined to save his family's legacy, forcing her to choose between her career and her heart.

When a driven career woman inherits a charming but dilapidated castle in Scotland, she travels there intending to sell it quickly. However, she finds herself captivated by the local culture and a handsome Scottish historian who helps her uncover the castle's secrets and her own heart's desires.
A group of friends reuniting for a Christmas getaway in a remote cabin find their holiday cheer turn to terror when a masked killer begins to stalk them, picking them off one by one in a deadly game.

Based on the viral New Yorker short story, this film follows the brief and unsettling relationship between a young college student and an older man she meets at the movie theater where she works, exploring the complexities of modern dating and perception.

A young woman discovers she is part of a long line of 'hushers' – individuals who can silence restless spirits. As she learns to control her powers, she must confront a powerful, malevolent entity threatening her small town on All Souls' Day.

An aspiring cellist inherits a cursed antique cello. As she plays it, her musical abilities soar to new heights, but she soon realizes that the instrument demands a terrible price, unleashing a dark force that threatens her sanity and her life.

A cynical, best-selling author known for his reclusive nature is forced by his publisher to participate in his hometown's Christmas festival to promote his new book. He reluctantly teams up with a cheerful event planner who helps him rediscover the holiday spirit and perhaps find love.

Set in a luxurious Swiss hotel on New Year's Eve 1999, the lives of wealthy guests and the staff who serve them intersect in a series of extravagant, comedic, and sometimes absurd events as they await the arrival of the new millennium.

In ancient times, a young warrior makes a sacred oath to protect a mystical artifact from falling into the hands of a tyrannical king and his dark sorcerer, embarking on a perilous journey filled with mythical creatures and epic battles.

A meticulous event planner, obsessed with creating the 'perfect' Christmas for her clients, finds her own holiday plans thrown into chaos by her eccentric family and a charming, free-spirited new acquaintance who teaches her the beauty of imperfection.

During a devastating storm, a family seeks refuge in a remote, fortified house owned by a reclusive survivalist. As the storm rages outside and supplies dwindle, tensions rise within, revealing dark secrets and a struggle for survival against both the elements and each other.

A skeptical woman, unlucky in love, unexpectedly matches with a man on a dating app who claims to be Santa Claus. As she gets to know him during the festive season, she must decide if he's truly the magical figure or just a charming eccentric, all while rediscovering her belief in Christmas magic.

titulo: Mr. Monk's Last Case: A Monk Movie
sinopsis: Adrian Monk, the brilliant but obsessive-compulsive detective, returns to solve one last, very personal case involving his beloved stepdaughter Molly, a journalist working on a story that hits too close to home.

A curious and adventurous young cave-dweller named Tuk embarks on a journey with his animal friends to discover the meaning behind a mysterious, recurring bright star in the sky, inadvertently inventing many of the traditions we now associate with the very first Christmas.

titulo: Diary of a Wimpy Kid Christmas: Cabin Fever
sinopsis: Greg Heffley is in big trouble after accidentally damaging property. When a massive snowstorm traps him and his family indoors for Christmas, he worries he won't get the presents he wants, all while trying to avoid his family's holiday antics and stay off Santa's naughty list.

Charlie Swift, a loyal fixer and hitman for an aging New Orleans mob boss, finds himself in a deadly predicament when a rival gang tries to eliminate his entire crew. He teams up with the ex-wife of a man he killed to seek revenge and uncover a deeper conspiracy.
